'''Adam Gierasch and Jace Anderson''' are a husband and wife writing team, known for their work in the horror genre.<ref>{{cite web|title=CBS Films Picks Up Superpower Spec 'Split' (Exclusive)|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/cbs-films-picks-up-superpower-613649|publisher=THR|accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref> Adam Gierasch is also known as an actor and director, and he released his [[directorial debut]] ''[[Autopsy (2008 film)|Autopsy]]'' in 2008.

==Filmography==
{{col-begin}}
{{col-2}}

===Films written together===
*''Spiders'' (2000, screenplay)
*''[[Crocodile (2000 film)|Crocodile]]'' (2000, screenplay)
*''Panic'' (2002, screenplay)
*''[[Crocodile 2: Death Swamp]]'' (2002, screenplay)
*''[[Derailed (2002 film)|Derailed]]'' (2002, screenplay)
*''Rats'' (2003, screenplay)
*''[[Toolbox Murders]]'' (2004)
*''[[Mortuary (2005 film)|Mortuary]]'' (2005)
*''[[Mother of Tears]]'' (2007)
*''[[Autopsy (2008 film)|Autopsy]]'' (2008)
*''[[Night of the Demons (2009 film)|Night of the Demons]]'' (2009)
*''[[Fertile Ground (film)|Fertile Ground]]'' (2011)
*''[[Fractured (film)|Fractured]]'' (2013)<ref>{{cite web|last=Turek|first=Ryan|title=First Photos from Schism Directed by Adam Gierasch|url=http://www.shocktillyoudrop.com/news/168853-first-photos-from-schism-directed-by-adam-gierasch/|publisher=STYD|accessdate=31 January 2014}}</ref>

===Anderson, as actor===
*''Thirsty'' (2009, voice of Slushy Cup)
*''[[Fertile Ground (film)|Fertile Ground]]'' (2011, as Headmistress in Photo)
*''This Week in Horror'' (2011, 1 episode, as herself)
*''FEARnet's Movies with More Brains'' (2011, as herself)
*''Into the Dark: Exploring the Horror Film'' (TBA, as herself)

===Anderson, as producer===
*''[[Fractured (film)|Fractured]]'' (2013)
*''[[House by the Lake]]'' (2015)
{{col-2}}

===Gierasch, as director===
*''[[Autopsy (2008 film)|Autopsy]]'' (2008, also scriptwriter)
*''[[Night of the Demons (2009 film)|Night of the Demons]]'' (2009, also screenplay)
*''[[Fertile Ground (film)|Fertile Ground]]'' (2011, also scriptwriter)
*''[[Fractured (film)|Fractured]]'' (2013, also scriptwriter)<ref>{{cite web|last=Gingold|first=Michael|title=Director reveals the naked truth about "FRACTURED"|url=http://www.fangoria.com/new/director-reveals-the-naked-truth-about-fractured/|publisher=Fangoria|accessdate=1 May 2014}}</ref>
*''[[House by the Lake]]'' (2015)<ref>{{cite web|last1=Turek|first1=Ryan|title=Adam Gierasch & Cast Check In at the House By the Lake|url=http://www.shocktillyoudrop.com/news/363297-adam-gierasch-cast-check-house-lake/|publisher=STYD|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref>
*''Tales of Halloween'' (2015, segment)<ref>{{cite web|last1=Yamato|first1=Jen|title=Barry Bostwick, Joe Dante, John Landis Set For ‘Tales Of Halloween’|url=http://deadline.com/2015/01/tales-of-halloween-anthology-barry-bostwick-joe-dante-john-landis-cast-1201344836/|publisher=Deadline|accessdate=17 January 2015}}</ref>

===Gierasch, as actor===
*''[[Asylum (1997 film)|Asylum]]'' (1997, as Ronald Briggs)
*''[[Martial Law (TV series)|Martial Law]]'' (1999, 1 episode, as Groomsman)
